Method - Any Name can be given
return the value/s
It can take arguments
Object has to be used for invoking

Constructor - A constructor is a unique function that gets called automatically when an object is created of a class. 
The main purpose of a constructor is to initialize or assign values to the data members of that class
Constructor name is fixed.
def __init__(self):

It 'll not return any value.
It can also take arguments.
Constructor 'll be called(Invoked) at the time of object creation itself. If the constructor has argument, then it has to be passed while creating the object.
